     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <pb facs="5"/>
   <lg>
      <l>YOu carelesse Church-men, that your time mis-spend</l>
      <l>In idlenesse, or worldly cogitation,</l>
      <l>Learne of the Learned in the Lawes, to spend</l>
      <l>Your idle time in holy Meditation.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Denout Ciuilians of our English Nation,</l>
      <l>Besides their true discharge of publique place,</l>
      <l>Giue faire example, worthy imitation,</l>
      <l>By learned Pen, to season soules with grace.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>
         <hi>Hayward,</hi> in Prose; our Authour here in Verse,</l>
      <l>Both Doctors of another facultie,</l>
      <l>Doe sacred heau'nly Mysteries reherse,</l>
      <l>As if they did professe Diuinitie.</l>
   </lg>
   <lg>
      <l>Goe on (braue Spirits) while your deuouter Lines</l>
      <l>Shame them that falsly call themselues Diuines.</l>
      <signed>A. Magirus.</signed>
   </lg>
</div>
